metadata.title: Cessna 152
aws::graph::propositions: # Cessna 152 Aircraft Models and Specifications
Cessna 152 was type approved in 1977.
Cessna 152 was produced as 1978 to 1985 model years.
Cessna 152 is approved for chandelles.
Cessna 152 is approved for steep turns.
Cessna 152 is approved for barrel rolls.
Cessna 152 is approved for snap rolls.
Cessna 152 is approved for loops.
Cessna 152 is approved for vertical reversements.
Cessna 152 is approved for lazy eights.
Cessna 152 is approved for spins.
Cessna 152 is approved for aileron rolls.
Cessna 152 is approved for Immelmann turns.
Cessna 152 is approved for Cuban eights.
Cessna 152 is approved for stalls except whip stalls.
F152 is a Reims-built Model 152.
552 F152 aircraft were built.
FA152 Aerobat is a Reims-built Model A152.
89 FA152 Aerobat aircraft were built.
C152 II is not a special model but has Nav Pac equipment package.
Nav Pac equipment package includes better quality avionics for Instrument Flight Rules flying.
Nav Pac equipment package includes additional interior equipment.
Additional interior equipment makes C152 II a little more basic weight.
C152 T is not a special model but has flight school equipment package.
"T" in C152 T denotes "trainer" and not a sub-model.
C152 Reimagined is not a special model but a general overhaul and rebuilt of Cessna 152s.
C152 Reimagined is done by Aviat.

text:
Type approved in 1977 and produced as 1978 to 1985 model years. The following aerobatic maneuvers are approved: chandelles, steep turns, barrel rolls, snap rolls, loops, vertical reversements, lazy eights, spins, aileron rolls, Immelmann turns, Cuban eights and stalls (except whip stalls).
F152
Reims-built Model 152, 552 built.
FA152 Aerobat
Reims-built Model A152, 89 built.
C152 II
Not a special model but with Nav Pac equipment package, which included better quality avionics for IFR flying and additional interior equipment, which makes it a little more basic weight.

C152 T
Not a special model but flight school equipment package, with "T" denoting "trainer" and not a sub-model.
C152 Reimagined
Not a special model but a general overhaul and rebuilt of Cessna 152s by Aviat.:
